  "body": "Hello,\r\n\r\n**Do you want to request a *feature* or report a *bug*?**\r\nReport a bug.\r\n\r\nI have stateless component like below:\r\n\r\n```\r\nconst Demo = (props) => {\r\n    let input, span;\r\n\r\n    const onChange = (e) => {\r\n        console.log(span); // null\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    return (\r\n        <div>            \r\n            <input type=\"file\" ref={e) => input = el } onChange={onChange} />\r\n            <span ref={el => span = el}></span>\r\n        </div >\r\n    )\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n**What is the current behavior?**\r\nSecond `ref` (_span_) is always `null`, but first one (_input_) is okay.\r\n\r\n**What is the expected behavior?**\r\nMultiple refs should work :p\r\n\r\n**Which versions of React, and which browser / OS are affected by this issue? Did this work in previous versions of React?**\r\n\r\n16.2.0/Firefox 60/Windows 10 x64/I don't know.\r\n\r\nThanks.",
